    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em>A broad-shouldered human man with short greying hair, a scar near his jawline, and tired eyes sharpened by years of night patrols. He wears a weathered city watch cloak over chain armor and carries an old lantern that casts a warm amber glow.</em></p><h3>Personality</h3><p>Quiet, vigilant, and deeply disciplined. Garron speaks with measured restraint and constantly watches his surroundings. He has little patience for corruption or cruelty, especially from those in authority.</p><h3>Motivation</h3><p>To protect ordinary citizens from the corruption festering inside the city watch and gather enough evidence to expose the former captain who betrayed his oath.</p><h3>Mannerisms</h3><p>Adjusts the lantern flame while thinking; pauses before entering dark streets; keeps one hand close to his staff at all times.</p><h3>Voice &amp; Accent</h3><p>Low, tired, steady. Speaks like someone used to giving patrol reports and short warnings.</p><h3>Bonds, Ideals, Flaws</h3><ul><li><strong>Bond:</strong> Garron still feels responsible for the younger guards he once trained. He secretly protects several witnesses tied to crimes committed by corrupt officers.</li><li><strong>Ideal:</strong> Justice means protecting people when institutions fail. Duty without integrity is worthless.</li><li><strong>Flaw:</strong> He struggles to trust authority figures and often works alone even when allies would help him.</li></ul><hr><h3>GM Notes</h3><p>Use Garron as a grounded urban protector NPC who can guide players through the darker parts of the city. He works well for investigation campaigns, corruption storylines, and morally gray city adventures.</p><h3>Secrets</h3><p>Garron possesses hidden records proving several city watch officers accepted bribes from smugglers and nobles. One missing witness could expose the entire network.</p><h3>Relationships</h3><p>Former City Watch Captain: hidden enemy and source of Garron's disgrace. Local citizens: cautious respect. Street vendors and night workers quietly support Garron. Marla Crowshade: mutual suspicion and wary respect — Garron has observed the unnatural blue lights from her ruined tower during his night patrols.</p><h3>Plot Hooks</h3><p>1. Garron asks the party to escort a frightened witness through dangerous alleys.\n2. A corrupt officer frames Garron for murder.\n3. Strange disappearances occur along Garron's old patrol route.\n4. Garron discovers evidence linking smugglers to the city council.</p><h3>Encounter Ideas</h3><p>1. Night patrol interrupted by an alley ambush.\n2. Investigation of a lantern signal system used by smugglers.\n3. Rooftop chase through foggy streets.\n4. Tense social encounter with corrupt guards at a checkpoint.</p>",
        "public": ""
      },
